# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.example (repo root) — frontend build / deploy environment
# Copy to .env for local overrides. NEVER commit the real .env.
#
# The API server has its OWN env file with the full set of server vars
# (DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, ADMIN_*, CORS_ORIGIN, SMTP_*, etc.):
#   → see server/.env.example
# This root file only holds build/deploy-time variables for the Vite frontend.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── App base URL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Canonical public base URL of the deployed app (frontend origin). The API server
# (server/index.js) reads this as the CORS_ORIGIN fallback AND to build the invite
# and password-reset links it emails (e.g. ${APP_BASE_URL}/reset?token=…). In
# production set to the HTTPS origin, e.g. https://pecanrev.com.
# (Full email/SMTP config lives in server/.env — see server/.env.example.)
APP_BASE_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# ── Vite (frontend) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only variables prefixed VITE_ are exposed to the client bundle at build time.
# The frontend currently calls the API via the relative /api path (proxied in
# dev by vite.config.js to 127.0.0.1:3001), so no VITE_ vars are required today.
# Add them here as they are introduced, e.g.:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL="/api"

# ── Sentry (frontend, 93.md §5.1 — OPTIONAL, disabled when unset) ──────────────
# DSN-gated: with VITE_SENTRY_DSN unset (the default) the Sentry SDK chunk is
# never downloaded and no network calls are made. These are BUILD-TIME values
# (inlined by Vite at `npm run build`), so staging builds must be built with
# the staging values. Use a SEPARATE Sentry project from the server; a DSN is
# not a secret, but keep real values out of git all the same.
# Full setup + scrubbing contract: docs/manager/sentry-setup.md.
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
# Environment tag shown in Sentry ("production" | "staging"); falls back to the
# Vite build MODE when unset.
# VITE_SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT="production"
# Performance tracing sample rate 0..1 — conservative default 0 (off).
# VITE_SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE=0

# ── Stitch MCP (DESIGN-TIME ONLY — never read by the app/server/bundle) ──────────
# The Stitch design source is reached through the Stitch MCP server, used only by
# Claude Code during design work. The API key is NEVER read by the application,
# the server, the Vite bundle, tests, or CI — keep it out of all of those.
#
# Configure the MCP at USER scope (stored in your local Claude config, NOT the
# repo) so the key never lands in git:
#   claude mcp add stitch --transport http \
#     --header "X-Goog-Api-Key: ${STITCH_API_KEY}" \
#     https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp
#
# Provide the key via your shell environment (export STITCH_API_KEY=…) — the line
# below is a SAFE PLACEHOLDER ONLY; do not paste a real key into any committed file.
STITCH_API_KEY=
